==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Experimental
<hw>Ex*per`i*men"tal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf.F.
<ets>exp⟦eacute⟧rimental</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to
experiment; founded on, or derived from, experiment or trial; <as>as,
<ex>experimental</ex> science</as>; given to, or skilled in, experiment;
<as>as, an <ex>experimental</ex> philosopher</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Known by, or derived from, experience; <as>as,
<ex>experimental</ex> religion</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>experimentalism</ent>⟦br⟧
